<p><font face="Arial" color="#004A95"><strong><big><big>The biggest party in Scotland. Ever!</big></big></strong></font></p>

<table border="0" width="750">
  <tr>
    <td width="115" valign="top" bgcolor="#002D42"><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">club
    beat news</font></td>
    <td width="417" bgcolor="#002D42"><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Report written by
      for clubber.co.uk</font><p><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">In what is tipped to be the most spectacular millennium event in Scotland, COLOURS are proud to present the marvellous, the magnificent, the majestic MASTERS OF THE MILLENNIUM. COLOURS are widely recognised as the most prolific club promoters in Scotland and have dominated the Scottish club scene for over 10 years. They have consistently staged the biggest and best parties in some of most outrageous venues in the country and this New Year will be no exception. MASTERS OF THE MILLENNIUM will see 15,000 clubbers unite in what promises to be a mammoth millennium meltdown in the heart of the Scotland. The state of the art venue, selected for its amazing location and vast capacity is situated in Lanarkshire, exactly 22 miles from both Glasgow and Edinburgh.<p> Spanned over an unbelievable 1 million sq feet, Centrelink is the UKs biggest indoor arena and you can bet it will be packed full of crazy capers including fairground attractions and a circus. Revellers will have a choice of five dance arenas at the Centrelink 5 Complex, from the DANCE ANTHEMS arena with Radio 1 FM’s DAVE PEARCE to the MINISTRY OF SOUND arena featuring the legendary DAVID MORALES via ISDN link, with further live links from New York, Sydney and Cape Town as they see in their own millenniums. <p> Although the full DJ line-up is yet to be announced, COLOURS have secured an enviable selection of exclusive appearances from some of the most distinguished deck technicians in the business as well as a surprise guest appearance from one of the UK’s greatest live bands. <p> A shuttle coach service comprising no less than 60 Arriva double deckers has been arranged to ferry folks to and from the arena to ensure that no-one misses out on the COLOURS centennial celebrations. Doors open at 6pm so get some comfy shoes on because this soiree won’t sleep until  8am on 1 January 2000. Tickets are now on sale priced between £60 and £90 depending on time of purchase, giving everyone the opportunity to be a part of this momentous occasion. Buy early to avoid disappointment and prepare to be taken on a millennium journey that will propel you into the next century in style. <p> FULL DJ LINE UP TO BE ANNOUNCED - We guarantee it'll be a big one, John!</font></p>
